<recipe>
<title>
Slow Cooker Barbecue Beef
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 10 minutes
COOK TIME: 8 hours
TOTAL TIME: 8 hours 10 minutes
COURSE: Main Course
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: beef, crock pot, slow cooker
SERVINGS: 8
</details>
<ingredients><ingredient amount="1.0">Onion</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0 Cup">Broth</ingredient></ingredients>
<instructions>
Add sliced onion to the bottom of slow cooker.
Place roast over sliced onions fat side down.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. I use about 1/2 teaspoon each salt and pepper.
Pour broth around the roast.
Cover, and cook on low for 8 hours or on high for 4 hours.
Shred meat and discard fat.
Return meat to slow cooker, and stir in *barbecue sauce.
Let sit in sauce about 30 minutes on low.
</instructions>
<cuisine>American</cuisine></recipe>